data.title: Library of Congress Finding Aids: Browse by Name
data.meta_description: Browse LC finding aids by name. Finding aids are XML documents created using the Encoded Archival Description (EAD). Creators, collectors, and other people or bodies represented in finding aids. Includes the names of individuals, families, and corporate bodies (organizations, government agencies, conferences, projects, events, and entities like ships and musical groups). Names are selected from controlled lists used by the Library of Congress.
